%N A394605 Decimal expansion of the mode of the distribution of distances between two points in a unit disk.
%C A394605 The mode of the probability density function f(s) = (1/Pi) * 2*s*(2*theta(s) - sin(2*theta(s))), for 0 <= s <= 2, and 0 otherwise, where theta(s) = arccos(s/2).
%H A394605 F. Garwood and J. C. Tanner, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/3610457">2800. On Note 2754: A Repeated Integral</a>, The Mathematical Gazette, Vol. 42, No. 342 (1958), pp. 292-293.
%F A394605 Equals 2*cos(x) where x is the unique positive zero of sin(2*x) - 2*x/3.
%e A394605 0.836222297968574770782434894770367711607229333496118...
%t A394605 RealDigits[With[{t = x /. FindRoot[Sin[2*x] == (2*x)/3, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]}, 2*Cos[t]]][[1]]
%o A394605 (PARI) {my(t = solve(x = 1, 3/2, sin(2*x) - 2*x/3)); 2 * cos(t)}
%Y A394605 Cf. A093070 (mean), A102519, A394606 (median), A394607 (square).
